data.description: Listen to this episode from The FADER Uncovered on Spotify. On the fifth episode of The FADER Uncovered podcast, host Mark Ronson is joined by Tame Imapala's Kevin Parker to look back at his band's 2012 FADER cover story and his journey from creating psych rock alone at home to becoming festival headlining rock star. Kevin tells Mark about celebrating 10 years of the band's debut album Innerspeaker, the key to writing a great song, and his memory of playing Coachella with Tyler, The Creator and Danny DeVito watching from the side of the stage.
